1
00:01:04,682 --> 00:01:08,978
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

2
00:01:17,022 --> 00:01:19,733
9 YEARS AGO

3
00:01:20,693 --> 00:01:22,319
I'm not a fan of shamanism.

4
00:01:23,237 --> 00:01:25,114
Can't you go in on your own?

5
00:01:25,197 --> 00:01:26,407
Seon.

6
00:01:26,490 --> 00:01:29,618
Anyone successful in Korea
consults a fortune-teller.

7
00:01:29,994 --> 00:01:32,830
My mom trusts Master Park
more than her lawyer.

8
00:01:33,581 --> 00:01:35,541
She credits her for making her rich.

9
00:01:35,874 --> 00:01:37,167
- "Rich?"
- Yes.

10
00:01:37,251 --> 00:01:40,254
So take the plunge and come with me.

11
00:01:40,629 --> 00:01:43,132
Who knows?
We might get some awesome news.

12
00:01:43,549 --> 00:01:45,134
I still don't like it.

13
00:01:45,217 --> 00:01:47,219
- It's a waste of money, too.
- What money?

14
00:01:47,303 --> 00:01:49,597
You don't have to pay
if you're with me.

15
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:52,349
I always came here with my mom.

16
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:55,644
It's my first time coming on my own,
and it's a bit scary.

17
00:01:56,437 --> 00:01:58,564
You're the only one I can ask.

18
00:02:00,107 --> 00:02:01,108
Okay, then.

19
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:04,820
CELESTIAL READER MASTER PARK

20
00:02:07,406 --> 00:02:08,616
How do you know each other?

21
00:02:09,491 --> 00:02:11,201
She's a good friend. Why?

22
00:02:12,661 --> 00:02:14,288
I see concern in your Four Pillars.

23
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,916
Your household will become dark

24
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,126
as if it were struck by lightning.

25
00:02:21,003 --> 00:02:23,297
What does that mean?

26
00:02:23,672 --> 00:02:26,175
Why did you come back
when you won't listen to me?

27
00:02:26,675 --> 00:02:29,345
I told you not to marry that fool.

28
00:02:30,262 --> 00:02:32,264
You said there was a way out.

29
00:02:32,348 --> 00:02:33,849
We already tied the knot.

30
00:02:34,391 --> 00:02:36,268
Your only way out

31
00:02:36,602 --> 00:02:37,811
is to have a child.

32
00:02:38,145 --> 00:02:39,980
But that's easier said than done.

33
00:02:40,522 --> 00:02:42,274
Your flame is already so weak.

34
00:02:42,358 --> 00:02:44,485
A tiny wisp of air could blow it out.

35
00:02:45,152 --> 00:02:46,236
What's that supposed to mean?

36
00:02:46,737 --> 00:02:48,781
Quit saying stuff I can't understand.

37
00:02:48,864 --> 00:02:50,991
Tell me what to do.
Write me a paper talisman.

38
00:02:51,450 --> 00:02:53,369
Not even the great Madam Jeon

39
00:02:53,452 --> 00:02:55,287
can talk her daughter
out of anything.

40
00:02:55,371 --> 00:02:57,581
What more could I say to you?

41
00:02:57,665 --> 00:03:00,084
You only remember what you like.

42
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:02,169
You can't talk to me like that.

43
00:03:02,252 --> 00:03:03,879
I've had enough of this.

44
00:03:03,962 --> 00:03:05,839
How dare you take that tone with me?

45
00:03:05,923 --> 00:03:06,924
- I...
- Yi-gyeong.

46
00:03:08,217 --> 00:03:10,552
You heard the way she talked.

47
00:03:11,053 --> 00:03:12,471
Am I the rude one here?

48
00:03:13,389 --> 00:03:14,973
Let's get out of here.

49
00:03:15,057 --> 00:03:17,559
You're the one
who needs to listen to me.

50
00:03:18,352 --> 00:03:19,353
What?

51
00:03:19,436 --> 00:03:21,939
Didn't your husband
spend a fortune recently?

52
00:03:22,690 --> 00:03:23,691
What was it on?

53
00:03:24,274 --> 00:03:25,401
A building?

54
00:03:27,820 --> 00:03:30,322
I see it.

55
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:33,742
I see it. I can see it.

56
00:03:40,457 --> 00:03:41,458
Handcuffs.

57
00:03:41,834 --> 00:03:42,960
Prison uniform.

58
00:03:43,877 --> 00:03:45,003
Handcuffs?

59
00:03:46,338 --> 00:03:49,007
If you don't do anything,
your husband will go to prison.

60
00:03:52,594 --> 00:03:56,014
He's a man who doesn't need laws
to live the straight and narrow.

61
00:03:56,598 --> 00:03:57,808
Do you want to go with him?

62
00:03:59,101 --> 00:04:00,102
What?

63
00:04:00,185 --> 00:04:01,478
Unless you want to join him

64
00:04:02,563 --> 00:04:03,814
buy a paper talisman.

65
00:04:06,442 --> 00:04:08,694
- Let's go, Yi-gyeong.
- Your kid's not well.

66
00:04:10,654 --> 00:04:15,159
That's because you met and married
when you shouldn't have.

67
00:04:18,787 --> 00:04:20,330
Let's see...

68
00:04:27,546 --> 00:04:29,298
It's prayer beads
made from a meteorite.

69
00:04:29,923 --> 00:04:31,258
Keep this on you.

70
00:04:32,217 --> 00:04:34,052
Good things will happen to your child

71
00:04:34,887 --> 00:04:36,638
and your husband will be fine.

72
00:04:37,264 --> 00:04:38,265
Take them.

73
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:41,101
Thanks.

74
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,520
A million won.

75
00:04:44,772 --> 00:04:45,773
What?

76
00:04:45,856 --> 00:04:47,524
You got a huge discount
for being a first-timer.

77
00:04:50,903 --> 00:04:51,904
What?

78
00:04:55,157 --> 00:04:56,283
Do as I said.

79
00:04:58,160 --> 00:05:03,415
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

80
00:05:05,459 --> 00:05:06,543
Mr. Gi?

81
00:05:06,835 --> 00:05:08,962
Hey, what are you doing?

82
00:05:09,463 --> 00:05:11,799
You aren't allowed to drink
at a convenience store these days.

83
00:05:11,882 --> 00:05:12,883
Is that so?

84
00:05:15,385 --> 00:05:17,304
I have something nice at my office.

85
00:05:17,930 --> 00:05:18,931
Come with me.

86
00:05:32,444 --> 00:05:36,281
M&amp;A REALTORS

87
00:05:38,492 --> 00:05:42,329
I bought this in Kyoto
to share with a special client.

88
00:05:45,958 --> 00:05:47,042
Here you go.

89
00:06:06,186 --> 00:06:08,397
Is something up, Hee-ju?

90
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,898
Sorry.

91
00:06:09,982 --> 00:06:11,483
The alcohol got to me fast.

92
00:06:18,156 --> 00:06:19,575
My goodness.

93
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:29,084
Mr. Gi.

94
00:06:30,294 --> 00:06:31,712
That Deputy Nam guy.

95
00:06:32,838 --> 00:06:34,381
Don't trust him too much.

96
00:06:35,173 --> 00:06:37,718
He's a psycho money-grabber.

97
00:06:38,302 --> 00:06:40,220
He'll do anything for money.

98
00:06:44,224 --> 00:06:45,225
Why say that?

99
00:06:48,812 --> 00:06:50,522
What is it? Is something wrong?

100
00:06:50,606 --> 00:06:52,441
You're just as bad.

101
00:06:52,524 --> 00:06:53,650
Why me?

102
00:06:55,736 --> 00:06:57,946
You said you'd cut me in.

103
00:06:58,780 --> 00:07:00,115
When we bought Hanmaeum Building.

104
00:07:00,198 --> 00:07:02,284
You said you'd give me a bonus.

105
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:04,786
This is insane! It's 30 billion won!

106
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:06,371
It's all thanks to you, Hee-ju.

107
00:07:06,455 --> 00:07:08,498
I'll get a bonus, right?

108
00:07:08,582 --> 00:07:10,125
Of course. Let's talk outside.

109
00:07:12,461 --> 00:07:14,796
Yes, right. I put it off too long.

110
00:07:15,255 --> 00:07:16,465
Let me see.

111
00:07:16,882 --> 00:07:18,508
I got your point.

112
00:07:18,592 --> 00:07:19,843
It was on my mind.

113
00:07:19,927 --> 00:07:20,928
Was it really?

114
00:07:21,261 --> 00:07:22,262
Here you go.

115
00:07:22,846 --> 00:07:24,473
Here are some gift certificates.

116
00:07:24,556 --> 00:07:26,350
They're valid at a lot of places

117
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:27,893
so you'll have no problem using them.

118
00:07:28,226 --> 00:07:29,353
Are you serious?

119
00:07:32,606 --> 00:07:33,774
- Whatever.
- Okay.

120
00:07:33,857 --> 00:07:35,025
Let's clink glasses.

121
00:07:35,108 --> 00:07:36,151
- Yes.
- Here.

122
00:07:36,234 --> 00:07:37,819
- You should have some more.
- Gosh.

123
00:07:38,570 --> 00:07:39,947
We can slow down.

124
00:07:40,781 --> 00:07:42,532
- To the redevelopment.
- To the redevelopment.

125
00:07:42,616 --> 00:07:45,661
Let it be fun, constructive

126
00:07:45,744 --> 00:07:47,788
- and a blessing to others.
- Okay.

127
00:07:47,871 --> 00:07:51,124
M&amp;A REALTORS

128
00:07:56,254 --> 00:07:57,255
Hee-ju.

129
00:07:58,715 --> 00:08:00,008
Do you know about love?

130
00:08:05,055 --> 00:08:06,056
What's going on?

131
00:08:06,765 --> 00:08:08,684
Do you have trouble with your wife?

132
00:08:09,935 --> 00:08:10,936
No.

133
00:08:13,438 --> 00:08:14,481
What's the matter?

134
00:08:14,564 --> 00:08:16,400
You know I have a good hunch.

135
00:08:16,817 --> 00:08:18,819
It's pretty obvious something's up.

136
00:08:19,277 --> 00:08:20,278
No.

137
00:08:21,780 --> 00:08:22,781
Is it an affair?

138
00:08:26,743 --> 00:08:27,744
An affair?

139
00:08:30,038 --> 00:08:31,999
Affairs, affairs.

140
00:08:32,082 --> 00:08:34,501
A wind of affairs is blowing.

141
00:08:35,794 --> 00:08:36,795
A wind.

142
00:08:36,878 --> 00:08:38,880
I'm right. It's about an affair.

143
00:08:39,423 --> 00:08:40,424
Who with?

144
00:08:40,507 --> 00:08:42,718
Is it you or her? Who's cheating?

145
00:08:43,427 --> 00:08:44,428
Hee-ju.

146
00:08:45,887 --> 00:08:46,930
Listen.

147
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:49,391
Legally speaking,
when you get divorced

148
00:08:50,017 --> 00:08:52,269
the one who had an affair
is the one at fault.

149
00:08:52,352 --> 00:08:55,480
That means the innocent one
is more advantageous

150
00:08:55,981 --> 00:08:57,315
when we divide the assets.

151
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:58,650
I didn't have an affair

152
00:08:59,109 --> 00:09:01,528
but Seon did.

153
00:09:02,112 --> 00:09:03,739
Who with?

154
00:09:05,532 --> 00:09:07,034
I can't tell you that.

155
00:09:09,036 --> 00:09:10,454
Oh, no.

156
00:09:14,166 --> 00:09:15,417
I'm the one who got cheated on.

157
00:09:16,293 --> 00:09:18,503
Why do I feel so cornered?

158
00:09:19,004 --> 00:09:20,714
No, you're not.

159
00:09:20,797 --> 00:09:22,883
You're not boxed in a corner.

160
00:09:23,175 --> 00:09:25,802
You said you did nothing wrong.

161
00:09:26,428 --> 00:09:29,473
Sue your wife and demand a divorce.

162
00:09:29,556 --> 00:09:33,018
When it comes to splitting assets
or custody arrangements

163
00:09:33,101 --> 00:09:35,645
you will have an advantage
over your wife.

164
00:09:37,272 --> 00:09:39,691
You seem to see one side
and not the other.

165
00:09:42,986 --> 00:09:44,696
Love is an absolute power.

166
00:09:45,781 --> 00:09:48,200
It ranks way above the law.

167
00:09:49,868 --> 00:09:52,537
The one who loves the other more
is always at a disadvantage.

168
00:09:54,414 --> 00:09:55,415
You see

169
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:58,251
I love my wife
more than she loves me.

170
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,170
I'm an idiot.

171
00:10:00,253 --> 00:10:01,880
Poor you.

172
00:10:05,258 --> 00:10:06,259
Goodness.

173
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:10,472
It must be so hard on you.

174
00:10:10,555 --> 00:10:14,935
- An affair...
- Oh, dear.

175
00:10:15,018 --> 00:10:17,604
A wind of affairs...

176
00:10:19,106 --> 00:10:22,192
- A gust of wind...
- An affair...

177
00:10:24,736 --> 00:10:25,737
An affair...

178
00:10:51,888 --> 00:10:53,223
The photo came out nicely.

179
00:10:58,019 --> 00:11:00,021
<i>I wish to expose</i>
<i>Pyeongbukgwan heiress</i>

180
00:11:00,105 --> 00:11:02,107
<i>Jeon Yi-gyeong's violent streak.</i>

181
00:11:06,903 --> 00:11:07,904
Mr. Gi.

182
00:11:11,992 --> 00:11:13,910
- Mr. Gi.
- Yes?

183
00:11:33,013 --> 00:11:34,139
Mr. Gi.

184
00:11:38,852 --> 00:11:42,230
MR. MIN HWAL-SUNG

185
00:11:44,608 --> 00:11:47,110
<i>Mr. Min, I've got something big.</i>

186
00:11:47,194 --> 00:11:48,737
<i>Would you like to strike a deal?</i>

187
00:11:52,908 --> 00:11:54,326
<i>We've been married for ten years.</i>

188
00:11:54,701 --> 00:11:58,246
<i>I was a victim of vicious</i>
<i>physical and verbal abuse</i>

189
00:11:58,330 --> 00:12:00,415
<i>along with repeated humiliation.</i>

190
00:12:00,498 --> 00:12:01,499
HEE-JU

191
00:12:06,046 --> 00:12:07,047
What's this?

192
00:12:07,672 --> 00:12:11,051
MR. MIN, I'VE GOT SOMETHING BIG

193
00:12:11,134 --> 00:12:14,471
WOULD YOU LIKE TO STRIKE A DEAL?

194
00:12:14,804 --> 00:12:17,224
She only texts
when she needs something.

195
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:21,311
What's he doing?

196
00:12:28,526 --> 00:12:29,527
<i>Hee-ju.</i>

197
00:12:30,946 --> 00:12:32,072
<i>Do you know about love?</i>

198
00:12:33,907 --> 00:12:34,908
<i>What's going on?</i>

199
00:12:35,617 --> 00:12:37,535
<i>Do you have trouble with your wife?</i>

200
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:44,709
M&amp;A REALTORS

201
00:12:44,793 --> 00:12:48,964
M&amp;A REALTORS

202
00:13:07,023 --> 00:13:09,109
<i>It's pretty obvious something's up.</i>

203
00:13:09,901 --> 00:13:12,821
A wind of affairs...

204
00:13:13,738 --> 00:13:16,658
- A gust of wind...
- An affair...

205
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,543
Hee-ju.

206
00:13:37,512 --> 00:13:38,513
Hee-ju.

207
00:13:39,597 --> 00:13:40,598
Hee-ju.

208
00:13:47,230 --> 00:13:48,231
Hee-ju.

209
00:13:49,065 --> 00:13:50,692
Man, what time is it?

210
00:13:53,987 --> 00:13:54,988
Hee-ju.

211
00:13:55,989 --> 00:13:57,115
Get up.

212
00:13:58,366 --> 00:13:59,367
Hee-ju.

213
00:14:21,389 --> 00:14:22,474
Get in.

214
00:14:40,617 --> 00:14:42,452
Why are you giving me that look?
It's uncomfortable.

215
00:14:43,453 --> 00:14:44,996
I liked you from the very start.

216
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:46,831
You what?

217
00:14:49,876 --> 00:14:53,213
I had a crush on you since the moment
Su-jong introduced us.

218
00:14:54,047 --> 00:14:56,549
You don't know how much I wished
you two would break up.

219
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,301
Stop it.

220
00:14:59,552 --> 00:15:01,137
What we did was a mistake.

221
00:15:01,513 --> 00:15:03,598
Before you two got married

222
00:15:03,932 --> 00:15:05,683
if I'd told you how I felt

223
00:15:07,352 --> 00:15:08,770
would we have gotten married?

224
00:15:09,604 --> 00:15:10,605
I'm going home.

225
00:15:12,690 --> 00:15:14,859
<i>Legally speaking,</i>
<i>when you get divorced</i>

226
00:15:14,943 --> 00:15:17,153
<i>the one who had an affair</i>
<i>is the one at fault.</i>

227
00:15:17,237 --> 00:15:19,322
<i>That means the innocent one</i>

228
00:15:19,406 --> 00:15:20,740
<i>- is more advantageous</i>
- What is this?

229
00:15:20,824 --> 00:15:21,991
<i>when we divide the assets.</i>

230
00:15:22,075 --> 00:15:23,910
Su-jong is getting ready
to divorce you.

231
00:15:23,993 --> 00:15:26,246
<i>But Seon did.</i>

232
00:15:26,329 --> 00:15:27,330
What?

233
00:15:27,414 --> 00:15:29,374
You're about to be backstabbed.

234
00:15:29,457 --> 00:15:30,542
<i>I can't tell you that.</i>

235
00:15:32,752 --> 00:15:34,129
<i>Oh, no.</i>

236
00:15:34,212 --> 00:15:36,714
Isn't this Hee-ju the realtor?

237
00:15:40,051 --> 00:15:41,594
You could get walked all over.

238
00:15:42,595 --> 00:15:43,930
Prepare yourself to divorce him.

239
00:15:45,473 --> 00:15:47,475
You already know
about the crimes Su-jong committed.

240
00:15:48,226 --> 00:15:51,146
Yi-gyeong's kidnapping
and Oh Dong-ki.

241
00:15:51,729 --> 00:15:53,148
My mother-in-law's death.

242
00:15:53,815 --> 00:15:55,650
We must use that to get leverage.

243
00:15:57,318 --> 00:15:58,403
I'll give you a hand.

244
00:16:06,494 --> 00:16:07,495
What are you doing?

245
00:16:10,874 --> 00:16:12,625
We know all about each other.

246
00:16:13,168 --> 00:16:14,169
Inside and out.

247
00:16:15,503 --> 00:16:17,172
Don't be silly. Get your hand off me.

248
00:16:18,882 --> 00:16:19,924
It's okay.

249
00:16:20,925 --> 00:16:22,510
Who would help you if not me?

250
00:16:23,511 --> 00:16:25,263
- Will you stop this?
- Come here.

251
00:16:25,722 --> 00:16:26,723
Get away from me.

252
00:16:28,766 --> 00:16:29,934
My nose!

253
00:16:30,018 --> 00:16:31,269
I'll ask him myself.

254
00:16:32,228 --> 00:16:33,688
Hey, Seon. Listen...

255
00:16:33,771 --> 00:16:35,106
Listen to me first, Seon!

256
00:16:38,651 --> 00:16:40,570
You need to prepare for divorce now

257
00:16:40,653 --> 00:16:42,322
to get the most you can!

258
00:16:44,657 --> 00:16:46,618
My offer to work together.

259
00:16:46,701 --> 00:16:48,661
It's still valid,
so think it through carefully.

260
00:16:51,164 --> 00:16:52,582
SEON

261
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,585
- Hey, Seon.
<i>- Hello?</i>

262
00:16:56,794 --> 00:16:58,963
- Who are you with right now?
<i>- Hang on.</i>

263
00:16:59,839 --> 00:17:01,591
Can you come to where I am?

264
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:03,468
Let's talk in person.

265
00:17:04,177 --> 00:17:05,303
Where are you?

266
00:17:06,429 --> 00:17:07,931
I'm at Hee-ju's realtor's office.

267
00:17:08,348 --> 00:17:09,474
<i>Okay, wait there.</i>

268
00:17:10,391 --> 00:17:11,392
Okay.

269
00:17:21,277 --> 00:17:24,614
M&amp;A REALTORS

270
00:17:27,951 --> 00:17:28,952
Su-jong.

271
00:17:37,168 --> 00:17:38,169
She's dead.

272
00:17:40,213 --> 00:17:41,214
Did you kill her?

273
00:17:41,297 --> 00:17:42,382
I'm not crazy.

274
00:17:49,514 --> 00:17:50,515
INCOMING CALL

275
00:18:00,275 --> 00:18:01,693
Darn it.

276
00:18:07,073 --> 00:18:09,492
She was dead when I woke up.

277
00:18:09,867 --> 00:18:12,203
I really didn't do anything.

278
00:18:14,539 --> 00:18:15,540
Hang on.

279
00:18:15,999 --> 00:18:17,250
What was "divide the assets" about?

280
00:18:17,959 --> 00:18:20,044
Did you tell Hee-ju
you wanted a divorce?

281
00:18:20,753 --> 00:18:22,046
How do you know about that?

282
00:18:22,714 --> 00:18:24,132
Hwal-sung told me.

283
00:18:25,592 --> 00:18:27,010
How did he know?

284
00:18:27,093 --> 00:18:29,721
He played a recording of your voice.

285
00:18:35,101 --> 00:18:36,102
Where's my share?

286
00:18:37,478 --> 00:18:39,439
Your share? What's that?

287
00:18:40,189 --> 00:18:41,816
We agreed to split it.

288
00:18:41,899 --> 00:18:44,319
That went out the window
the moment you called the police.

289
00:18:44,402 --> 00:18:45,528
I explained.

290
00:18:45,612 --> 00:18:47,780
I didn't call them.
My mother-in-law did.

291
00:18:47,864 --> 00:18:49,574
You're talking your way out again.

292
00:18:50,617 --> 00:18:52,035
Hwal-sung did this.

293
00:18:52,535 --> 00:18:53,536
Did what?

294
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,163
Well...

295
00:18:55,246 --> 00:18:56,748
Not long ago

296
00:18:57,332 --> 00:18:59,751
he came to me and asked
for his share of my property.

297
00:18:59,834 --> 00:19:02,754
He kicked up a fuss,
and I turned him down.

298
00:19:03,504 --> 00:19:06,257
He plans to create a rift between us

299
00:19:06,341 --> 00:19:09,469
to take Se-yoon Building from me.

300
00:19:11,054 --> 00:19:12,388
But that...

301
00:19:12,889 --> 00:19:15,058
What does that have to do
with Hee-ju's death?

302
00:19:15,141 --> 00:19:17,977
Would Hee-ju have given him
that recording for free?

303
00:19:18,770 --> 00:19:21,272
She demanded something
in exchange for it

304
00:19:21,356 --> 00:19:23,566
and that blew up into a fight.

305
00:19:24,150 --> 00:19:25,443
While I was asleep

306
00:19:25,526 --> 00:19:26,944
they talked about shares
and the recording

307
00:19:27,028 --> 00:19:28,237
and then this happened.

308
00:19:30,990 --> 00:19:32,408
That's just too insane.

309
00:19:32,825 --> 00:19:35,703
Would Hwal-sung
kill someone over that?

310
00:19:35,787 --> 00:19:36,871
Don't you know what he's like?

311
00:19:37,747 --> 00:19:39,582
Don't you remember
he planned the kidnapping?

312
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:41,501
I'm going to divorce Yi-gyeong.

313
00:19:42,377 --> 00:19:43,795
We'll both get divorced

314
00:19:45,505 --> 00:19:46,798
and take over

315
00:19:47,590 --> 00:19:48,591
the redevelopment project.

316
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:51,469
With the right plan

317
00:19:52,011 --> 00:19:53,221
we can pull it off.

318
00:19:55,306 --> 00:19:57,642
Once he gets
his share in the business

319
00:19:58,101 --> 00:20:00,520
he'll grab me by the throat
and strangle me.

320
00:20:03,064 --> 00:20:05,149
I wonder where Hee-ju's phone is.

321
00:20:09,821 --> 00:20:10,863
What are you doing?

322
00:20:10,947 --> 00:20:12,115
Her phone.

323
00:20:12,198 --> 00:20:13,991
I want to see the call log.

324
00:20:18,162 --> 00:20:19,163
Come here, Seon.

325
00:20:20,039 --> 00:20:21,833
Hello? Is anyone inside?

326
00:20:26,295 --> 00:20:27,505
Darn it.

327
00:20:31,134 --> 00:20:32,135
Hang on.

328
00:20:36,222 --> 00:20:37,932
What's going on?

329
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,234
Is he gone?

330
00:20:49,652 --> 00:20:51,404
- Yes.
- Are you sure?

331
00:20:51,779 --> 00:20:52,864
Yes, he's gone.

332
00:20:55,658 --> 00:20:56,659
Seon.

333
00:20:59,370 --> 00:21:00,371
Do you trust me?

334
00:21:02,957 --> 00:21:03,958
What?

335
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,501
You don't trust me?

336
00:21:07,879 --> 00:21:09,213
When you're drunk

337
00:21:10,131 --> 00:21:12,341
- you do sleep through anything.
- Right.

338
00:21:13,259 --> 00:21:14,469
I swear.

339
00:21:16,012 --> 00:21:18,222
I have no memory of anything
after I fell asleep.

340
00:21:31,694 --> 00:21:32,862
Why? What is it?

341
00:21:32,945 --> 00:21:34,238
<i>Ms. Kim.</i>

342
00:21:34,322 --> 00:21:35,323
<i>Where are you?</i>

343
00:21:35,406 --> 00:21:37,283
<i>We're celebrating</i>
<i>Da-rae getting into Harvard.</i>

344
00:21:37,366 --> 00:21:38,493
<i>You're coming, right?</i>

345
00:21:38,576 --> 00:21:40,495
- S-jong, she got in.
- What?

346
00:21:40,578 --> 00:21:41,579
Da-rae got in.

347
00:21:41,662 --> 00:21:43,414
- She did?
- Hang on.

348
00:21:44,999 --> 00:21:46,125
DA-RAE'S ACADEMY TEACHER

349
00:21:46,209 --> 00:21:48,628
<i>Da-rae got in?</i>
<i>Did you hear from them?</i>

350
00:21:49,462 --> 00:21:50,588
<i>You didn't know?</i>

351
00:21:51,255 --> 00:21:53,007
<i>She received</i>
<i>the acceptance e-mail last night.</i>

352
00:21:53,424 --> 00:21:55,176
<i>I'll forward you</i>
<i>the one they sent us.</i>

353
00:21:55,676 --> 00:21:56,677
Her letter of acceptance.

354
00:21:59,555 --> 00:22:01,307
Da-rae did it.

355
00:22:02,266 --> 00:22:04,018
This is incredible.

356
00:22:04,519 --> 00:22:05,520
Hang on.

357
00:22:06,395 --> 00:22:07,772
If they sent the e-mail last night

358
00:22:07,855 --> 00:22:09,398
why didn't Da-rae say anything?

359
00:22:09,649 --> 00:22:11,692
She didn't say? Was she busy?

360
00:22:12,485 --> 00:22:15,905
No, she was in her room all night.

361
00:22:17,782 --> 00:22:19,325
Make a video call.

362
00:22:21,661 --> 00:22:29,085
MY LOVING DAUGHTER

363
00:22:29,585 --> 00:22:31,337
- Why won't she pick up?
- She won't answer.

364
00:22:36,259 --> 00:22:37,510
There's no response.

365
00:22:37,593 --> 00:22:38,803
Darn it.

366
00:22:49,146 --> 00:22:50,731
I WANT TO BE ALONE

367
00:22:54,110 --> 00:22:55,611
Congratulations on getting in, kids.

368
00:22:55,695 --> 00:22:58,197
I knew you'd make it.

369
00:22:58,489 --> 00:22:59,532
Applause.

370
00:23:00,408 --> 00:23:01,409
Congratulations.

371
00:23:01,492 --> 00:23:02,827
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

372
00:23:03,870 --> 00:23:06,372
Congratulations on getting in.

373
00:23:06,455 --> 00:23:11,669
I knew you'd get it done, Da-rae.

374
00:23:13,588 --> 00:23:16,090
Da-rae, Jeong-min, Bo-mi.
Blow out the candles.

375
00:23:16,173 --> 00:23:17,174
Get ready.

376
00:23:17,258 --> 00:23:19,260
WE HAVE BRAGGING RIGHTS FOREVER!
WE'RE GOING TO THE IVY LEAGUE!

377
00:23:19,343 --> 00:23:20,344
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

378
00:23:20,428 --> 00:23:22,054
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

379
00:23:22,138 --> 00:23:23,472
Congratulations!

380
00:23:23,723 --> 00:23:25,391
- I'm dead jealous.
- Seriously.

381
00:23:25,641 --> 00:23:26,642
- Congratulations.
- Seriously.

382
00:23:26,726 --> 00:23:27,977
- Congratulations.
- Good for you.

383
00:23:28,603 --> 00:23:30,730
<i>Da-rae, why aren't you picking up?</i>

384
00:23:31,647 --> 00:23:33,065
Do you want soda?

385
00:23:33,149 --> 00:23:34,317
- I'll have some.
- What about you?

386
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,401
Are you all right?

387
00:23:36,652 --> 00:23:38,613
- I've been waiting to dig in.
- Give me some, too.

388
00:23:38,696 --> 00:23:39,780
Okay, hang on.

389
00:23:48,748 --> 00:23:51,292
YOU KILLED ME

390
00:23:55,087 --> 00:23:58,633
MY MOTHER-IN-LAW, AND THE CAFÉ OWNER

391
00:24:07,058 --> 00:24:08,351
What are you thinking about?

392
00:24:16,192 --> 00:24:17,526
JUST... ABOUT THE TUITION?

393
00:24:17,610 --> 00:24:19,278
Your father owns a building.

394
00:24:19,570 --> 00:24:20,696
Why would you worry?

395
00:24:24,450 --> 00:24:26,118
The others ordered some food.

396
00:24:26,202 --> 00:24:27,286
Do you want to join them?

397
00:24:28,329 --> 00:24:29,330
Let's go.

398
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:40,216
It's a shame she's dead,
but it can't be helped.

399
00:24:40,716 --> 00:24:41,717
Right.

400
00:24:43,427 --> 00:24:44,637
What can't be helped?

401
00:24:47,014 --> 00:24:48,182
Let's clean it up.

402
00:24:50,351 --> 00:24:52,520
M&amp;A REALTORS

403
00:24:52,603 --> 00:24:54,897
All the cameras in the neighborhood

404
00:24:55,272 --> 00:24:57,608
will have filmed you
coming in here with her.

405
00:25:00,987 --> 00:25:04,615
M&amp;A REALTORS

406
00:25:05,950 --> 00:25:06,951
That's right.

407
00:25:07,702 --> 00:25:09,161
We drank, I passed out

408
00:25:09,245 --> 00:25:11,580
and she was dead when I woke up.

409
00:25:13,124 --> 00:25:15,126
I was recently a kidnapping suspect

410
00:25:15,584 --> 00:25:17,336
and was even interrogated about it.

411
00:25:18,087 --> 00:25:20,047
I can't think of a way out.

412
00:25:20,548 --> 00:25:21,924
You said you thought
Hwal-sung did it.

413
00:25:23,467 --> 00:25:25,678
Won't his arrest solve everything?

414
00:25:26,470 --> 00:25:29,640
At least we'll get to find out
what happened during the night.

415
00:25:29,932 --> 00:25:32,351
We must identify the murderer.

416
00:25:33,227 --> 00:25:36,063
Or at least find proof
that it wasn't you.

417
00:25:37,690 --> 00:25:39,984
It would be best for Hee-ju
if we were to find out

418
00:25:40,901 --> 00:25:42,403
who did this to her.

419
00:25:52,913 --> 00:25:53,914
Seon.

420
00:25:55,583 --> 00:25:57,001
Thank you for trusting me.

421
00:25:58,419 --> 00:26:00,713
We'll talk again
after we sort this out.

422
00:26:01,714 --> 00:26:03,257
We need Da-rae to go to Harvard.

423
00:26:04,008 --> 00:26:05,009
Right.

424
00:26:07,219 --> 00:26:08,304
So...

425
00:26:09,930 --> 00:26:11,599
We have a place to hide her.

426
00:26:12,099 --> 00:26:13,768
The problem is, how do we move her?

427
00:26:26,947 --> 00:26:27,948
What are you doing?

428
00:26:29,075 --> 00:26:30,284
Strip her, Su-jong.

429
00:26:30,367 --> 00:26:31,368
What?

430
00:26:31,660 --> 00:26:33,079
Take her clothes off.

431
00:26:41,420 --> 00:26:42,463
- Her car key.
- Yes.

432
00:26:42,755 --> 00:26:43,756
Okay.

433
00:27:44,108 --> 00:27:45,776
- Su-jong, let's go.
- Okay.

434
00:27:45,860 --> 00:27:49,280
I can't find her phone.
Someone must've taken it.

435
00:27:49,363 --> 00:27:50,364
Let's go for now.

436
00:28:30,863 --> 00:28:32,364
Is this the right way?

437
00:28:33,699 --> 00:28:35,117
We must go home first.

438
00:28:36,410 --> 00:28:38,078
We need to be seen
on our neighborhood cameras.

439
00:28:39,496 --> 00:28:42,082
You two get out first,
then meet me at the back.

440
00:28:43,334 --> 00:28:44,543
Okay.

441
00:29:33,092 --> 00:29:34,093
Careful.

442
00:29:48,607 --> 00:29:49,608
I'll get down first.

443
00:29:58,033 --> 00:29:59,285
She's so heavy.

444
00:30:03,038 --> 00:30:04,164
Get in.

445
00:30:13,632 --> 00:30:14,633
Let's go.

446
00:30:27,813 --> 00:30:31,233
PROVIDE A MEASURE!

447
00:30:31,317 --> 00:30:34,737
DO NOT DRIVE US OUT!

448
00:30:56,216 --> 00:30:57,718
See if anyone is coming.

449
00:30:58,969 --> 00:31:00,304
- No one's around.
- Wait.

450
00:31:00,721 --> 00:31:01,722
Hold on.

451
00:31:06,477 --> 00:31:07,853
Wait, what do we do now?

452
00:31:07,936 --> 00:31:08,937
One second.

453
00:31:09,646 --> 00:31:11,398
- Let's get her closer.
- Closer?

454
00:31:11,482 --> 00:31:12,733
- Just a little more.
- Okay.

455
00:31:12,816 --> 00:31:13,984
Get her closer.

456
00:31:14,985 --> 00:31:16,070
Closer.

457
00:31:16,153 --> 00:31:17,654
Get her closer.

458
00:31:18,113 --> 00:31:19,156
Closer.

459
00:31:19,490 --> 00:31:20,574
Can you lift her?

460
00:31:22,868 --> 00:31:24,078
Are we allowed to do this?

461
00:31:25,037 --> 00:31:26,038
Let's see.

462
00:31:38,675 --> 00:31:39,676
Su-jong.

463
00:31:40,427 --> 00:31:42,262
- Let me get changed first.
- Okay.

464
00:31:43,472 --> 00:31:47,476
KEEP OUT

465
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:01,323
Handcuffs.

466
00:32:01,698 --> 00:32:02,699
Prison uniform.

467
00:32:03,534 --> 00:32:04,535
Handcuffs?

468
00:32:04,618 --> 00:32:07,079
If you don't do anything,
your husband will go to prison.

469
00:32:08,414 --> 00:32:09,665
Keep this on you.

470
00:32:09,748 --> 00:32:11,667
<i>Good things will happen to your child</i>

471
00:32:12,084 --> 00:32:13,836
<i>and your husband will be fine.</i>

472
00:32:34,148 --> 00:32:35,149
Are we done?

473
00:32:35,649 --> 00:32:36,650
Yes.

474
00:32:38,569 --> 00:32:39,695
I have no idea

475
00:32:39,945 --> 00:32:41,780
what I'm doing right now.

476
00:32:42,156 --> 00:32:44,283
I'm sorry.
I'll make sure I catch the culprit.

477
00:32:46,034 --> 00:32:47,286
I'll report you

478
00:32:47,786 --> 00:32:49,538
if you don't.

479
00:32:49,788 --> 00:32:52,124
Yes, pin this on me.

480
00:32:52,416 --> 00:32:54,084
I won't tell them that you helped.

481
00:32:55,586 --> 00:32:57,004
What do you mean?

482
00:32:57,296 --> 00:32:58,922
How am I your accomplice?

483
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:01,675
I didn't say you were.

484
00:33:03,802 --> 00:33:05,471
Forget it. Good grief.

485
00:33:13,645 --> 00:33:14,897
MY LOVING DAUGHTER

486
00:33:17,065 --> 00:33:18,484
Su-jong, look.

487
00:33:18,567 --> 00:33:20,068
I got a message from Da-rae.

488
00:33:20,569 --> 00:33:23,697
MOM, I KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN YOU AND YI-GYEONG

489
00:33:24,281 --> 00:33:25,282
What is this?

490
00:33:27,075 --> 00:33:28,577
Wait, how did she know?

491
00:33:30,537 --> 00:33:31,663
I have no idea.

492
00:33:32,414 --> 00:33:33,540
What?

493
00:33:33,624 --> 00:33:36,084
She won't reply to my message
or pick up her phone.

494
00:33:37,503 --> 00:33:40,339
- I need to go and see her right now.
- Yes, Seon.

495
00:33:40,422 --> 00:33:42,508
Grab a cab.
I have to get rid of the car.

496
00:33:42,591 --> 00:33:44,426
- You should go.
- Yes, okay.

497
00:33:47,471 --> 00:33:48,972
Hello, Da-rae's teacher?

498
00:33:49,056 --> 00:33:51,683
I just saw the text message.

499
00:33:53,227 --> 00:33:54,853
Where should I go?

500
00:34:00,067 --> 00:34:01,860
Darn it.

501
00:34:03,946 --> 00:34:05,572
- Eat some chicken.
- I want the drumstick.

502
00:34:06,323 --> 00:34:07,991
- Here it is.
- That's so unfair.

503
00:34:08,867 --> 00:34:10,994
<i>What do you mean you know everything?</i>

504
00:34:11,828 --> 00:34:13,330
- What do you want?
- Soda.

505
00:34:13,413 --> 00:34:14,414
Soda?

506
00:34:14,498 --> 00:34:15,541
I KNOW...

507
00:34:15,624 --> 00:34:17,334
- He's taking the first sip.
- It doesn't matter.

508
00:34:17,709 --> 00:34:18,710
Unbelievable.

509
00:34:18,794 --> 00:34:22,089
I KNOW WHAT YOU AND DAD DID

510
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:24,883
You need to share.

511
00:34:25,634 --> 00:34:28,720
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
MOM

512
00:34:30,347 --> 00:34:31,557
- Stop it.
- What?

513
00:34:31,640 --> 00:34:32,724
Cut it out!

514
00:34:43,277 --> 00:34:45,112
- Soda, please.
- Did you eat this again?

515
00:34:45,195 --> 00:34:46,363
How many pieces did you eat?

516
00:34:46,822 --> 00:34:47,906
- Three.
- Three?

517
00:34:53,036 --> 00:34:54,413
Please take one.

518
00:34:54,496 --> 00:34:55,706
ANTI-DEVELOPMENT COMMITTEE

519
00:34:55,789 --> 00:34:57,291
- Thank you.
- Sure.

520
00:34:57,374 --> 00:35:00,002
UNITE AND FIGHT

521
00:35:00,085 --> 00:35:01,336
Please put one on your head.

522
00:35:01,587 --> 00:35:02,629
This is for you.

523
00:35:06,258 --> 00:35:08,093
MISSED CALLS
SU-JONG, SEON

524
00:35:11,305 --> 00:35:12,306
Did you all receive one?

525
00:35:12,389 --> 00:35:13,390
- Yes.
- Yes.

526
00:35:13,473 --> 00:35:17,227
Please raise your voice
as loudly as you can.

527
00:35:17,311 --> 00:35:18,478
- Yes!
- Okay!

528
00:35:18,562 --> 00:35:20,272
Should we practice?

529
00:35:20,355 --> 00:35:21,356
- Okay.
- Okay.

530
00:35:22,316 --> 00:35:26,320
We oppose forced development projects
that rob private property!

531
00:35:26,403 --> 00:35:28,572
- We oppose!
- We oppose!

532
00:35:28,655 --> 00:35:30,616
Suspend all destruction of history!

533
00:35:30,699 --> 00:35:32,618
We shall defend our buildings
with our lives!

534
00:35:32,701 --> 00:35:34,703
- We shall defend!
- We shall defend!

535
00:35:34,995 --> 00:35:36,288
I love the volume today.

536
00:35:37,289 --> 00:35:39,708
- Please keep this up.
- Yes.

537
00:35:39,791 --> 00:35:41,418
- We got this! Let's go!
- Let's go!

538
00:35:41,501 --> 00:35:43,670
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

