Is everything okay with your parents?

802
00:54:10,484 --> 00:54:14,447
(I have to tell you something.)

803
00:54:16,657 --> 00:54:21,370
(I want to apologize)

804
00:54:21,454 --> 00:54:24,832
(on behalf of my mom and dad.)

805
00:54:27,543 --> 00:54:29,670
Why are you apologizing
on their behalf?

806
00:54:31,672 --> 00:54:38,095
(What they did was wrong,
but they didn't do it intentionally.)

807
00:54:38,637 --> 00:54:42,641
(They feel bad
for what they did to you.)

808
00:54:47,521 --> 00:54:48,898
They feel bad?

809
00:54:51,025 --> 00:54:52,359
That's so easy.

810
00:54:52,902 --> 00:54:55,654
You can act like a piece of trash
and just feel bad about it.

811
00:54:57,364 --> 00:54:58,365
Da-rae.

812
00:55:00,242 --> 00:55:01,494
Do you want to live with me?

813
00:55:02,787 --> 00:55:04,997
You already know
what your parents did.

814
00:55:06,040 --> 00:55:07,458
Can you still live with them?

815
00:55:08,083 --> 00:55:09,919
I don't have any family

816
00:55:10,377 --> 00:55:12,046
and you practically don't, either.

817
00:55:13,547 --> 00:55:15,174
So let us be family.

818
00:55:15,716 --> 00:55:17,676
I'll pay for your study abroad.

819
00:55:18,093 --> 00:55:19,094
How about it?

820
00:55:20,095 --> 00:55:21,680
All you need to say is yes.

821
00:55:22,723 --> 00:55:24,099
Just give up on your mom and dad.

822
00:55:29,563 --> 00:55:33,234
(I can't. How can I do that?)

823
00:55:42,409 --> 00:55:47,122
YOU SAID A FAMILIAL RELATIONSHIP
IS ABOUT ACCEPTING LIMITATIONS

824
00:55:50,084 --> 00:55:51,293
I knew you'd say that.

825
00:55:54,338 --> 00:55:56,090
Then you're partially responsible

826
00:55:57,466 --> 00:55:58,968
for things that are about to happen.

827
00:57:40,736 --> 00:57:42,780
SEON

828
00:57:52,414 --> 00:57:53,707
<i>The call cannot be connected.</i>

829
00:58:01,507 --> 00:58:02,508
Hey.

830
00:58:02,716 --> 00:58:03,842
<i>Where are you?</i>

831
00:58:04,385 --> 00:58:06,762
I met with Hwal-sung,
and he didn't know anything.

832
00:58:06,845 --> 00:58:08,138
<i>That's not the problem.</i>

833
00:58:08,222 --> 00:58:11,350
But this punk is always lying,
so I find him hard to believe.

834
00:58:11,934 --> 00:58:13,352
<i>I think Da-rae got kidnapped.</i>

835
00:58:13,435 --> 00:58:14,436
What?

836
00:58:16,313 --> 00:58:17,523
It's Da-rae!

837
00:58:17,940 --> 00:58:20,150
I think Da-rae got kidnapped!

838
00:58:21,318 --> 00:58:22,319
What?

839
00:58:22,403 --> 00:58:23,654
What happened to Da-rae?

840
00:58:24,488 --> 00:58:26,824
I'm going to the police station now

841
00:58:26,907 --> 00:58:28,826
so come quickly, okay?

842
00:59:13,620 --> 00:59:14,621
Da-rae.

843
00:59:17,916 --> 00:59:18,917
Good job.

844
00:59:48,655 --> 00:59:51,575
MAD CONCRETE DREAMS

845
00:59:51,825 --> 00:59:53,077
<i>Was she really abducted?</i>

846
00:59:53,160 --> 00:59:54,870
<i>Yi-gyeong wouldn't do that.</i>

847
00:59:54,953 --> 00:59:56,705
<i>Things can't get any worse.</i>

848
00:59:56,789 --> 00:59:57,873
<i>I've already hit rock bottom.</i>

849
00:59:57,956 --> 01:00:01,376
<i>I just need your mom and dad</i>
<i>to be as broken as I am.</i>

850
01:00:01,460 --> 01:00:02,920
Da-rae knows everything, Su-jong.

851
01:00:03,003 --> 01:00:05,130
Sir, how old is your child?

852
01:00:05,214 --> 01:00:06,215
It hasn't been born yet.

853
01:00:06,548 --> 01:00:08,175
<i>Do you have newborn items?</i>

854
01:00:08,425 --> 01:00:09,426
<i>Who are you?</i>

855
01:00:09,510 --> 01:00:10,719
<i>Why are you doing this to me?</i>

856
01:00:10,803 --> 01:00:12,429
No!

857
01:00:12,513 --> 01:00:14,723
<i>Hwal-sung, I need you to die today.</i>

858
01:00:14,807 --> 01:00:16,892
I fully admit to murdering

859
01:00:16,975 --> 01:00:18,435
Jeon Yi-gyeong's husband,
Min Hwal-sung

860
01:00:18,519 --> 01:00:19,520
and abandoning his body.

861
01:00:32,658 --> 01:00:34,660
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
